    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An accelerator button sends an action when the user first clicks the button and continues sending actions until pressure on the button is released entirely."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For continuous accelerator buttons (see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nscontrol/1428952-continuous"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "), the interval between repeating actions (a rate typically specified with "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsbutton/1526612-setperiodicdelay"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") automatically adjusts to match the applied pressure.  As the user force clicks (presses harder), actions are sent more rapidly. As the user reduces pressure on the button, actions slow down. As such, the user has direct control over how fast actions are sent. Continuous accelerator buttons are intended for continuously advancing through a series of discrete objects, such as photos in an album or pages in a book."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For noncontinuous accelerator buttons, actions are sent whenever a change in force occurs. Noncontinuous accelerator buttons are intended for adjusting the speed of navigation, such as playback speed in a media player, based on pressure. Once the button is released, a final action is sent."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For buttons that are not accelerator buttons, the value of the button matches its state. For accelerator buttons, the value of the button is distinct from its state, and indicates pressure level. While the user force clicks the button, "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nscontrol/1428942-doublevalue"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is a measurement of pressure between "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "1.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and approaching "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "2.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". When released, "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "doubleValue"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An accelerator button appears like any other button and does not provide any visual indication that it supports variable pressure. To provide this type of visual indication, you can apply a custom "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsbutton/1534221-image"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to the button."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "On a system that doesn’t support pressure sensitivity, an accelerator button behaves like a button of type "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsmomentarylightbutton"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
